#DStv403 CAPE TOWN - The king of tennis, Roger Federer, has arrived in South Africa ahead of his sold-out Match in Africa against Rafael Nadal. Federer, who has won a record 20 Grand Slams, will play his first-ever match in sub-Saharan Africa on Friday. Federer and billionaire philanthropist, Bill Gates will face off with South African Daily Show host, Trevor Noah and Rafael Nadal. It's expected to set a new world record for spectators watching a tennis match. The Roger Federer Foundation is aimed at providing education for those less fortunate in Africa and Switzerland.